---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Learn more about Daniel Deepak.">
  <div class="py-12 md:py-20">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16 items-start">
      <!-- Photo -->
      <div class="flex justify-center md:justify-start">
        <img
          src="/images/placeholder-avatar.svg"
          alt="Daniel Deepak"
          class="w-64 h-64 rounded-2xl shadow-lg object-cover"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Bio -->
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">About Me</h1>

        <div class="prose space-y-6">
          <p>
            I'm Daniel Deepak, and I'm fascinated by how people think, how markets work,
            and how the right tools can change everything.
          </p>

          <p>
            For the past decade, I've been building products, studying mental models, and
            documenting the journey. This blog is my space to share ideas that I think
            matter—things I've learned from building, from reading, and from talking with
            people who are doing interesting things.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8">What I Believe</h2>

          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li>
              <strong>Clarity is rare.</strong> Most people haven't thought deeply about what
              they believe or why they're building what they're building. I write to think
              clearly.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Tools shape thinking.</strong> The right tool doesn't just save time—it
              changes how you approach a problem. That's why I'm obsessed with productivity
              and workflow optimization.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>First principles matter.</strong> In a world of conventional wisdom and
              inherited constraints, the ability to think from first principles is a
              superpower.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Building in public builds trust.</strong> Transparency, honesty about
              progress, and showing your work are underrated competitive advantages.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8">Currently</h2>

          <p>
            I'm focused on understanding how to build sustainably, how to make decisions
            with incomplete information, and how to create something that matters to people.
          </p>

          <p>
            When I'm not thinking about these things, you'll find me reading, experimenting
            with new tools and workflows, or documenting insights that might be useful to
            others.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8">Get In Touch</h2>

          <p>
            If you're thinking about similar things or want to discuss ideas, I'd love to
            hear from you. Reach out on{' '}
            <a href="https://twitter.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              Twitter/X
            </a>{' '}
            or{' '}
            <a href="https://linkedin.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              LinkedIn
            </a>
            .
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  :global(.prose) {
    color: #333;
  }

  :global(.prose a) {
    color: #2563eb;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  :global(.prose a:hover) {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  :global(.prose h2) {
    color: #0a0a0a;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  :global(.prose ul) {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  :global(.prose li) {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  :global(.prose strong) {
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  :global(.prose p) {
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
</style>
